Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Directive 82/471/EEC of 30 June 1982 concerning certain products used in animal nutrition (1), as last amended by Commission Directive 89/520/EEC (2), and in particular Article 6 thereof,
Whereas Directive 82/471/EEC provides for regular amendment of the content of the Annex thereto as a result of developments in scientific or technical knowledge;
Whereas the study of two new products belonging to the group of protein products obtained from micro-organisms and the amino acids group has shown that these products fulfill the requirements of Directive 82/471/EEC; whereas the use of these products in animal nutrition should, therefore, be permitted under certain conditions;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Directive are in accordanced with the opinion of the Standing Committee for Feedingstuffs,
